>
  <p>I'm Wes Baker, tabletop gamer, miniature painter, and perpetually optimistic dungeon master. I've been playing RPGs since the mid-90s and painting miniatures for nearly as long, though my backlog would suggest otherwise.</p>

  <p>This site is where I write about the games I'm running, the models I'm painting, and the occasional board game that earns a spot on the small table in my office.</p>

  <h2 id="what-im-running">What I'm running</h2>

  <p>Right now I'm deep into <em>Keep on the Borderlands</em> with my kids: six sessions in, one player death, zero regrets. Before that we ran a short Shadowdark campaign that ended badly for everyone involved, which is to say it ended perfectly.</p>

  <p>On the adult side, I've been in a Pathfinder 2e campaign for about two years. I play a thaumaturge. It's going fine.</p>

  <h2 id="what-im-painting">What I'm painting</h2>

  <p>Currently working through a Nighthaunt warband for Warcry. I have a problem with buying models faster than I paint them, which is a problem I suspect is not unique to me.</p>

  <h2 id="the-site">The site</h2>

  <p>Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and hosted on <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com">Cloudflare Pages</a>. Search is <a href="https://pagefind.app">Pagefind</a>. The typeface is Cartridge by Connary Fagen, paired with <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Lora">Lora</a> for body text.</p>

  <p>Source is on <a href="https://github.com/wesbaker/wanderingreferee.com">GitHub</a> if you're curious.</p>
</BasePageLayout>
